01:26:43.679 --> 01:26:47.360
Father Lord, I believe, but help my unbelief.

01:26:53.221 --> 01:26:54.123
I'm telling you, I see the glory.

01:26:58.639 --> 01:27:01.800
I see the old become the new, the old generation.

01:27:01.800 --> 01:27:04.160
All of them, they're the great cloud of witnesses.

01:27:04.160 --> 01:27:05.120
We're the closers.

01:27:05.120 --> 01:27:13.280
There's so much of our family that are watching over right now.

01:27:13.280 --> 01:27:15.506
They're watching and we're closing this thing up.

01:27:27.280 --> 01:27:27.552
I see the river and I see the well at ORU again.

01:27:27.552 --> 01:27:30.409
And I see Oral Roberts drinking from that well.

01:27:30.409 --> 01:27:31.636
I see it right there.

01:27:43.211 --> 01:27:43.474
And Kenneth Hagin and all the greats that have passed on before, they're drinking their little cup, but the Lord said, 'It's time to go to the depth of the well.

01:27:43.474 --> 01:27:47.880
It's time to taste and see that the Lord is good in your life today.

01:27:47.880 --> 01:27:50.903
Taste and see that the Lord is good.

01:27:50.903 --> 01:28:01.440
He came to set the captives free, to bring sight to the blind, for his yoke is easy and his burden is light.

01:28:01.440 --> 01:28:05.573
Come unto me and I will give you rest.

01:28:05.573 --> 01:28:08.133
Take my yoke upon you.

01:28:08.133 --> 01:28:11.059
' We were singing that song two nights ago.

01:28:11.059 --> 01:28:16.329
'I am weak and lonely and my burden's light.

01:28:16.329 --> 01:28:19.280
Take my yoke upon you.

01:28:19.280 --> 01:28:20.680
' Oh Father, come unto me.

01:28:33.383 --> 01:28:33.611
I feel his presence so strong right now.

01:28:33.611 --> 01:28:37.880
Glory to God that he wants to come and visit us.

01:28:37.880 --> 01:28:39.463
I just sit there.

01:28:39.463 --> 01:28:44.879
Father, I love you and we worship you today.

01:28:44.879 --> 01:28:46.900
He's so real to me.

01:28:46.900 --> 01:28:51.086
Most people I look at say the supernatural is more real to me than the natural.

01:28:53.360 --> 01:28:53.680
You say, 'Well, good for you, Brendan.

01:28:53.680 --> 01:28:59.982
' No, he wants to have that with you.

01:29:04.846 --> 01:29:05.131
You just have to sit at his feet.

01:29:05.131 --> 01:29:11.326
How hungry, how desperate, how bad do you want change in your life?

01:29:11.326 --> 01:29:13.965
Are you fed up with your circumstances?

01:29:14.342 --> 01:29:15.349
That's where he's at.

01:29:15.349 --> 01:29:17.920
At the place of surrender, of just selling out for Jesus.

01:29:17.920 --> 01:29:21.332
He told me, he said, 'Brandon, I need more of you.

01:29:21.332 --> 01:29:23.360
' That's part of what I saw.

01:29:34.080 --> 01:29:34.280
I saw the beautiful purples in the trees.

01:29:34.280 --> 01:29:35.166
I see lavender.

01:29:42.971 --> 01:29:43.234
I could see the beautiful colors.

01:29:44.320 --> 01:29:46.420
And he was talking to me about the end times.

01:29:46.420 --> 01:29:55.1000
And it sounds so out there, but I was looking at the beautiful trees and I was looking in the field the other day and I could see the purple and I could see the lavenders.

01:29:59.591 --> 01:30:02.899
I could see all the colors and he was talking about the supernatural and it's the way he talks to me, and he loves colors, fragrance.

01:30:02.899 --> 01:30:03.979
It's being intimate with him.

01:30:07.669 --> 01:30:08.091
Having an intimacy with God.

01:30:13.012 --> 01:30:14.719
I read George Washington Carver's book, The Man Who Talked to the Flowers.

01:30:22.301 --> 01:30:22.577
And I longed for that when he said, 'Dear Creator...

01:30:22.577 --> 01:30:25.040
' He talked to the peanut.

01:30:34.711 --> 01:30:34.916
And I thought, 'Lord, if you do that with him, you'll do it with me.

01:30:34.916 --> 01:30:42.239
You're no respecter of persons, but you are a respecter of faith and those that pursue you.

01:30:42.239 --> 01:30:46.079
How hard, how bad, how desperate are you for change in your life?

01:30:46.079 --> 01:30:52.420
' And so I set out to it and I said, 'Lord, I set out to do this.

01:30:52.420 --> 01:30:55.040
I'm going to fast something every other day.

01:30:55.040 --> 01:30:59.581
' And I set out for that for a long time.

01:30:59.581 --> 01:31:01.600
I did that for years seeking him.

01:31:01.600 --> 01:31:04.613
But I always keep the main thing the main thing.

01:31:04.613 --> 01:31:05.466
Keeping him first.

01:31:05.466 --> 01:31:06.536
All this stuff.

01:31:18.540 --> 01:31:18.760
It's not about works.

01:31:25.093 --> 01:31:25.359
Your self-righteousness is as filthy rags.

01:31:25.359 --> 01:31:29.440
No matter how much you try to impress him, you're never going to impress him.

01:31:29.440 --> 01:31:31.439
'Oh, you did it.

01:31:34.320 --> 01:31:34.560
Let me give you an applause.

01:31:34.560 --> 01:31:36.347
' No, it's all about him.

01:31:37.360 --> 01:31:38.080
It's his grace on my stinkiness.

01:31:38.080 --> 01:31:44.834
Thank you, Father, that you look past all of it by your blood when I take communion.

01:31:44.834 --> 01:31:57.199
No matter how messed up I come to you, just as I am without one plea, that blood was shed for me.

01:31:57.199 --> 01:32:00.800
Thank you, Lord.

01:32:02.660 --> 01:32:04.359
I pass all my issues and I come in by your blood.

01:32:04.359 --> 01:32:11.000
That's why I take communion all the time because I'm flawed.

01:32:27.290 --> 01:32:27.620
I'm messed up without it.

01:32:46.159 --> 01:32:46.399
And without his grace, without his blood, I say, 'Lord, I just want to be more.

01:32:46.399 --> 01:32:48.133
I want to come up higher.

